🚀 GitHub Profile Viewer (Android App)

A modern Android application built using **Jetpack Compose** that allows users to search GitHub profiles and explore their data in a clean, fast, and interactive UI.


✨ Features

* Search GitHub users by username
* View user profile (avatar, name, bio, stats)
* View repositories (sorted by latest update)
* Open repositories in browser


👥 Social Features

* Followers screen
  * Clean card-based UI
  * Skeleton loading (shimmer)
  * Fetch additional user details
* Following screen
  * Fully implemented
  * Reuses UI components for consistency


⚡Performance & UX

* Skeleton loading UI for smooth experience
* Prevents duplicate API calls (optimized fetching)
* Shared caching for user details
* Smooth navigation between screens


💾 Storage & Handling

* Recent searches stored locally (SharedPreferences)
* Internet connectivity check before API calls
* Graceful error handling:
  * User not found
  * Network issues


🎨 UI & Design

* Material 3 design system
* Clean card-based layouts
* Consistent spacing and alignment
* Language color indicators for repositories
* Custom app icon


🛠 Tech Stack

* Kotlin
* Jetpack Compose
* MVVM Architecture
* Retrofit (GitHub REST API)
* Gson (JSON parsing)
* Coil (Image loading)
* Navigation Compose
* Coroutines


📂 Project Structure

com.example.githubprofileviewer
│
├── data/               # API & Retrofit setup
├── ui/                 # Screens (Main, Profile, Followers, Following)
│   ├── components/     # Reusable UI components (FollowerItem, etc.)
│   └── theme/          # Colors, typography, theming
├── utils/              # Network & helper utilities
├── MainViewModel.kt    # Business logic & state management
├── UiState.kt          # UI state handling


🧠 Architecture

This app follows MVVM (Model-View-ViewModel):

* View (UI) → Jetpack Compose screens
* ViewModel → Handles business logic, API calls, and state
* Model → API response data

🔥 Key Architecture Decisions

* Centralized `userDetails` cache to avoid duplicate API calls
* Reusable composables (e.g., `FollowerItem`)
* State-driven UI using `UiState`

⚙️ How It Works

1. User enters a GitHub username
2. App navigates to profile screen
3. API fetches:
   * User details
   * Repositories
4. Additional screens:
   * Followers → loads list + user details
   * Following → same optimized flow
5. UI reacts to state:
   * ⏳ Loading → Skeleton UI
   * ✅ Success → Data displayed
   * ❌ Error → Friendly message


